.TH man 1 "15 April 2020" "1.0" "Simple Shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B Simple Shell
- Interface for execute commands.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[path] [command_string -flags]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Simple Shell hsh
Receives a command and execute it showing the output in screen.
.SH COMMANDS
The following commands are some examples of the commands that can be performed by the Simple Shell
.I hsh:

-ls

-pwd

-cp

-mv

-cat

-less

-mkdir

-rm

For more information about the commands and their options 
.I (flags)
please type man and the name of the command.
.SH EXECUTION METHODS
.B Interactive Mode

Run the shell and type the commands to perform:

-$ ./hsh

-$ ls

-$ file1 file2 file3 folder1

-$ exit

.B Non-Interactive Mode

Pass the commands to perform and run the shell:

-$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

-$ hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

-$ exit

Or

-$ cat test_ls_2

-$ /bin/ls

-$ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh

-$ hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.SH Bugs
No known bugs.
